    {
      "id": "p3-note",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1015,
      "y": 760,
      "width": 410,
      "height": 140,
      "text": "🧠 Why most keys stay:\n• A key moves only if w(K, D) > previous winner's weight.\n• On average D steals 1/(N+1) of the keys.\n• Here only K3 because D's weight (0.99) > A (0.95).\n\n👉 New node = fair share, not a stampede.",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#cdd6f4",
